WEBVTT

00:03.583 --> 00:05.542
LATER.

00:07.458 --> 00:09.000
OK, SO LET ME
GET THIS STRAIGHT.

00:09.000 --> 00:11.708
OH, NO. WHY DO I FEEL
A QUASI-FEMINIST RANT
COMING ON?

00:11.708 --> 00:12.875
SHUT UP.

00:12.875 --> 00:15.708
SO BASICALLY,
SPRING BREAK IS
HUNTING SEASON,

00:15.708 --> 00:16.667
FLORIDA
IS THE FOREST,

00:16.667 --> 00:17.667
AND GIRLS
ARE THE TARGET.

00:17.667 --> 00:18.667
JO, YOU'RE ACTING
AS IF THE GIRLS

00:18.667 --> 00:19.208
DON'T HAVE A CHOICE
IN THE MATTER.

00:19.208 --> 00:20.834
OH, SURE THEY DO.

00:20.834 --> 00:21.959
YOU KNOW, THEY COULD
EITHER HOOK UP

00:21.959 --> 00:24.041
WITH THE DRUNK JOCK
FROM ARIZONA STATE

00:24.041 --> 00:25.125
OR THE DATE-RAPIST-
IN-TRAINING

00:25.125 --> 00:27.250
FROM THE NEAREST
COMMUNITY COLLEGE.

00:27.250 --> 00:29.333
OR THEY CAN STAY HOME
AND STUDY,

00:29.333 --> 00:30.458
WHICH, COME TO
THINK OF IT,

00:30.458 --> 00:32.250
DOES NOT SOUND
LIKE SUCH A BAD IDEA.

00:32.250 --> 00:33.583
WOULD YOU
JUST GO  ALREADY?

00:33.583 --> 00:35.291
HAVE FUN.
YOU DESERVE IT.

00:38.083 --> 00:40.667
CAN'T YOU JUST SKIP THAT
BIG HOLLYWOOD MEETING
AND COME WITH US?

00:40.667 --> 00:42.166
FOR THE UMPTEENTH TIME,

00:42.166 --> 00:43.583
IT'S NOT A BIG
HOLLYWOOD MEETING.

00:43.583 --> 00:45.375
WE'RE SIMPLY GOING TO NEW YORK
TO MEET AN AGENT

00:45.375 --> 00:46.792
WHO IS INTERESTED
IN THE MOVIE.

00:46.792 --> 00:48.667
MAKE THAT THE ONLY  AGENT
WHO IS INTERESTED IN THE MOVIE.

00:48.667 --> 00:50.959
DAWSON, IT'S HUGE.

00:50.959 --> 00:51.917
EVERYTHING
YOU'VE WORKED FOR,

00:51.917 --> 00:53.333
EVERYTHING
YOU'VE EVER WANTED,

00:53.333 --> 00:54.250
IT'S HAPPENING BECAUSE
YOU MADE IT HAPPEN.

00:54.250 --> 00:56.208
YOU DID IT AND
I'M VERY PROUD OF YOU.

00:56.208 --> 00:57.625
WELL, THANK YOU,
BUT IT'S NOT--

00:57.625 --> 01:00.125
NO! I WILL
NOT LET ANOTHER
SELF-DEPRECATING WORD

01:00.125 --> 01:02.000
COME OUT OF YOUR MOUTH.

01:02.000 --> 01:04.875
YOU RULE. YOU ROCK.
YOU ARE A GOLDEN GOD.

01:04.875 --> 01:06.375
NOW, ACCEPT IT.

01:12.208 --> 01:13.625
YOU KNOW WHO'D REALLY GET
A KICK OUT OF ALL THIS?

01:13.625 --> 01:15.500
WHO?

01:15.500 --> 01:17.125
MITCH.

01:19.625 --> 01:21.583
YEAH.

01:22.708 --> 01:24.291
YEAH, HE WOULD HAVE.

01:24.291 --> 01:26.583
HE WOULD'VE.
HE ABSOLUTELY
WOULD HAVE.

01:26.583 --> 01:31.458
HE WOULD HAVE--
HE WOULD HAVE TALKED
MY EAR OFF ABOUT IT.

01:31.458 --> 01:33.166
HE WOULD'VE HAD TO
KNOW THE AGENT.

01:33.166 --> 01:35.083
HE'D HAVE TO KNOW
HIS CLIENT LIST.
I'D HAVE TO--

01:35.083 --> 01:37.208
HE'D PROBABLY MAKE ME DO
A PRACTICE RUN WITH HIM.

01:38.750 --> 01:40.625
IT'S WEIRD.

01:40.625 --> 01:41.792
WHAT'S THAT?

01:41.792 --> 01:45.917
YOU'VE HAD THIS YEAR,
THIS COMPLETELY AWFUL YEAR,

01:45.917 --> 01:51.333
AND YET SOMEHOW EVERYTHING
WORKED OUT FOR THE BEST,
YOU KNOW?

01:54.375 --> 01:55.458
THAT'S ONE WAY
OF LOOKING AT IT.

01:55.458 --> 01:56.792
YOU DON'T THINK?

01:59.917 --> 02:02.208
ALL I KNOW IS
I CAME BACK FROM L.A.
FOR A REASON,

02:02.208 --> 02:05.417
A VERY SIMPLE,
VERY SPECIFIC REASON.

02:05.417 --> 02:07.041
I FEEL BAD, SOMETIMES--

02:07.041 --> 02:09.166
A LOT OF TIMES,
ACTUALLY--

02:09.166 --> 02:12.792
FOR HOW I MADE YOU FEEL
AFTER HE DIED.

02:12.792 --> 02:16.708
I'VE NEVER HELD IT AGAINST YOU,
NOT FOR A SINGLE SECOND.

02:16.708 --> 02:19.417
YOU DID WHAT YOU HAD TO DO
TO GET THROUGH IT.

02:19.417 --> 02:21.125
YEAH.

02:21.125 --> 02:22.875
AND...

02:22.875 --> 02:24.125
WHAT?

02:25.792 --> 02:29.417
I DON'T KNOW. SOMETIMES
I THINK IT'S BETTER...

02:29.417 --> 02:32.750
WHEN WE DON'T GET
TO TOUCH OUR DREAMS.

02:34.083 --> 02:35.375
DO YOU REALLY
BELIEVE THAT?

02:37.917 --> 02:41.625
I DON'T KNOW. NO. YES.

02:41.625 --> 02:43.417
I SPEND HALF THE TIME
WONDERING WHAT MIGHT HAVE BEEN

02:43.417 --> 02:47.542
AND THE OTHER HALF THINKING
"JUST AS WELL."

02:52.083 --> 02:53.750
DO YOU THINK
WE'LL EVER GET IT RIGHT?

02:56.333 --> 02:57.333
NOT IN THIS LIFETIME.

02:57.333 --> 02:58.417
HOW 'BOUT THE NEXT ONE?

02:58.417 --> 03:00.291
OR THE ONE AFTER THAT,
WHEN WE'RE BOTH CATS.

03:05.834 --> 03:08.792
OK, SERIOUSLY...

03:08.792 --> 03:09.792
GOOD LUCK.

03:09.792 --> 03:11.708
THANK YOU.

03:11.708 --> 03:13.333
YOU, TOO. HAVE FUN, OK?

03:13.333 --> 03:14.291
REMEMBER THE SUNBLOCK
AND BRING ME BACK
A SOUVENIR.

03:14.291 --> 03:17.000
PREFERABLY SOMETHING
OF THE, YOU KNOW,

03:17.000 --> 03:20.000
"MY SOULMATE WENT TO FLORIDA
AND ALL I GOT WAS THIS LOUSY
T-SHIRT" VIBE.

03:21.667 --> 03:22.875
GOODBYE.

04:14.208 --> 04:15.083
ARE YOU AWARE THAT
YOU HAVEN'T SAID ONE WORD

04:15.083 --> 04:17.583
IN AN HOUR AND A HALF?

04:17.583 --> 04:19.250
I'M LISTENING
TO THE RADIO.

04:19.250 --> 04:21.333
I TURNED IT OFF
20 MINUTES AGO.

04:23.583 --> 04:24.500
OH.

04:26.667 --> 04:28.250
SO WHAT ARE YOU
THINKING ABOUT?

04:28.250 --> 04:31.542
OR SHALL I SAY, "WHO"?

04:31.542 --> 04:32.500
NOBODY.

04:32.500 --> 04:36.083
OK. BUT IF YOU'RE NOT
GONNA TALK TO ME

04:36.083 --> 04:37.583
I MAY HAVE TO SING.

04:37.583 --> 04:39.083
BE MY GUEST.

04:39.083 --> 04:42.792
[IMITATING ELVIS]
♪ DAWSON, WE'RE ON THE HIGHWAY ♪

04:42.792 --> 04:46.625
♪ WE'RE GONNA GET
A LITTLE BIT OF--♪

04:46.625 --> 04:47.959
STOP. JOEY.

04:47.959 --> 04:49.542
WHAT WAS--?

04:49.542 --> 04:50.750
I WAS THINKING
ABOUT JOEY.

04:50.750 --> 04:52.333
DON'T EVER DO THAT
AGAIN, PLEASE.

04:52.333 --> 04:53.291
INTERESTING.

04:53.291 --> 04:57.291
THE DOE-EYED BRUNETTE,
HMM?

04:57.291 --> 04:58.125
SO WHAT'S THE STORY
ON THAT ONE?

04:58.125 --> 05:00.542
IT'S A VERY LONG STORY.

05:00.542 --> 05:04.291
DOES IT LOOK LIKE
I'M GOING ANYWHERE, SPORT?

05:09.458 --> 05:12.250
ALL RIGHT. STOP ME
WHEN YOU GET CONFUSED.

05:12.250 --> 05:16.875
I JUST DON'T THINK
IT'S A GOOD IDEA FOR ME
TO SLEEP OVER ANYMORE.

05:16.875 --> 05:20.208
I JUST THINK OUR EMERGING
HORMONES ARE DESTINED
TO ALTER OUR RELATIONSHIP

05:20.208 --> 05:24.792
AND I'M TRYING TO
LIMIT THE FALLOUT.

05:24.792 --> 05:27.417
THINGS CHANGE, DAWSON.
EVOLVE.

05:45.333 --> 05:47.083
JOEY! UP HERE!

05:47.083 --> 05:48.208
JOEY!

05:48.208 --> 05:51.250
HEY! HELLO!

05:51.250 --> 05:53.750
AAH! AAH! AHH!

05:53.750 --> 05:56.250
[LAUGHING]

05:56.250 --> 05:59.500
HEY, SCRUMPTIOUS.

05:59.500 --> 06:01.250
I WAS KINDA...

06:01.250 --> 06:02.667
IN THE MIDDLE...

06:02.667 --> 06:03.708
OF DOING SOMETHING.

06:03.708 --> 06:06.458
MMM. MY GOD,
I LOVE THIS BED.

06:06.458 --> 06:08.500
THIS BED IS BIGGER
THAN MY ENTIRE ROOM.

06:08.500 --> 06:11.917
YEAH, PLUS, MY PARENTS
PUT ONE OF THOSE FOAMY
EGG CRATES UNDERNEATH,

06:11.917 --> 06:12.834
SO IT'S SUPER COMFY.

06:12.834 --> 06:14.792
YOUR PARENTS
ARE WONDERFUL PEOPLE.

06:14.792 --> 06:16.291
WELL, I'LL TELL THEM
YOU SAID SO.

06:16.291 --> 06:16.500
YOU DO THAT.

06:21.083 --> 06:22.583
DO YOUR PARENTS
EVEN KNOW WHO I AM?

06:22.583 --> 06:25.375
DO YOUR PARENTS
KNOW WHO I AM?
NOPE.

06:25.375 --> 06:26.417
WELL,
NEITHER DO MINE.

06:26.417 --> 06:27.458
I DIDN'T THINK SO.

06:30.542 --> 06:31.542
I MEAN...

06:31.542 --> 06:34.375
WHAT WOULD I
EVEN TELL THEM
ABOUT YOU?

06:34.375 --> 06:37.333
WELL, YOU COULD TELL THEM
THAT I'M GOOD IN BED.

06:37.333 --> 06:39.834
THAT  WOULD
GO OVER HUGE.

06:42.500 --> 06:43.875
REALLY, WHAT WOULD
YOU TELL YOUR PARENTS
ABOUT ME?

06:43.875 --> 06:45.917
NOTHING.

06:45.917 --> 06:47.792
RIGHT.
RIGHT.

06:50.875 --> 06:52.792
THAT'S RIGHT, RIGHT?

06:52.792 --> 06:54.583
RIGHT. YES.
OBVIOUSLY.

06:54.583 --> 06:55.750
RIGHT, 'CAUSE CORRECT ME
IF I'M WRONG,

06:55.750 --> 06:57.041
BUT THE LAST THING THAT
PARENTS WANT TO HEAR ABOUT

06:57.041 --> 07:00.333
IS HOW MUCH PREMARITAL SEX
THEIR CHILDREN ARE HAVING.

07:00.333 --> 07:02.250
YEAH, ESPECIALLY
WITH SOME GUY

07:02.250 --> 07:04.250
WHO'S NOT EVEN
MY BOYFRIEND.

07:04.250 --> 07:05.667
I MEAN, OFFICIALLY.

07:05.667 --> 07:06.625
EXACTLY.

07:08.792 --> 07:10.375
EXACTLY.

07:13.500 --> 07:14.625
WELL, I APPRECIATE
YOU LETTING ME KNOW.

07:19.875 --> 07:20.875
FOUND HIM!

07:20.875 --> 07:24.166
OK. BYE.

07:24.166 --> 07:25.667
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING UP THERE?

07:25.667 --> 07:27.417
NOTHING.
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

07:27.417 --> 07:28.625
WELL, WE'RE GONNA
PICK ROOMS

07:28.625 --> 07:29.917
AND WE THOUGHT THAT WE'D
"ROCK, PAPER, SCISSORS"

07:29.917 --> 07:31.083
FOR THE WATERBED SUITE.

07:31.083 --> 07:32.125
YOU KNOW WHAT, JUST--

07:32.125 --> 07:33.041
TAKE WHATEVER YOU WANT.

07:33.041 --> 07:34.375
ALL RIGHT? I GOTTA
GO TO THE MARKET

07:34.375 --> 07:36.417
AND GET THE NECESSARY
PROVISIONS.

07:37.583 --> 07:39.583
OH, CAN YOU GET
SOME YOGURT?
YEAH.

07:39.583 --> 07:40.750
HOLD ON, ALL RIGHT?

07:40.750 --> 07:42.417
I SAID THE NECESSARY
PROVISIONS, ALL RIGHT?

07:42.417 --> 07:44.125
THAT'S BEER
AND THAT'S JELL-O.
THAT'S IT.

07:44.125 --> 07:48.458
OK. IF I GIVE YOU MONEY,
WOULD YOU PICK UP SOME
COLD MEDICINE FOR ME, TOO?

07:48.458 --> 07:51.250
I SORT OF FEEL SOMETHING
COMING ON AND I'D REALLY
LIKE TO NIP IT IN THE BUD.

07:51.250 --> 07:52.083
YEAH, JUST
GIMME THE MONEY.

07:52.083 --> 07:53.834
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

07:54.208 --> 07:55.708
[RING]

07:59.458 --> 08:00.417
HELLO.

08:00.417 --> 08:01.792
HELLO, GORGEOUS.

08:01.792 --> 08:04.625
SO, I WAS BEGINNING TO WORRY.
YOU HAVEN'T CALLED FOR 3 HOURS.

08:04.625 --> 08:06.542
OH, SO YOU DO
LIKE MY CALLING.

08:06.542 --> 08:08.542
WHAT DO YOU WANT, EXACTLY?

08:08.542 --> 08:11.166
NOTHING, REALLY.
JUST YOUR ADDRESS.

08:11.166 --> 08:14.667
NO PROBLEM. I'M AT
359 NO-WAY-IN-HELL AVENUE

08:14.667 --> 08:16.667
ON THE CORNER OF
GET-OVER-IT AND MAIN.

08:16.667 --> 08:18.291
YOU KNOW,
YOU CHALLENGE ME,
JOEY POTTER.

08:18.291 --> 08:19.750
I THOUGHT WE AGREED
TO TAKE A BREAK

08:19.750 --> 08:20.708
FROM THESE INCESSANT
PHONE CALLS.

08:20.708 --> 08:23.708
LOOK, I WOULD BE HAPPY
TO STOP CALLING.

08:23.708 --> 08:25.708
JUST TELL ME WHERE YOU ARE.

08:25.708 --> 08:28.166
I'M IN YOUR DREAMS,
CHARLIE TODD.

08:28.166 --> 08:32.332
SEE, NOW, WAIT A SECOND.
THAT SOUNDED SUSPICIOUSLY
LIKE FLIRTING TO ME.

08:32.332 --> 08:33.667
MAYBE...

08:33.667 --> 08:35.958
AND THIS IS WHAT
A DIAL TONE SOUNDS LIKE.

08:47.667 --> 08:49.166
SO THIS IS
SPRING BREAK, HUH?

08:49.166 --> 08:51.000
YUP.

08:51.000 --> 08:53.166
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY,
IT DOESN'T REALLY LOOK
LIKE THE BROCHURES.

08:53.166 --> 08:54.834
HEY, I PROVIDED
THE HOUSE.

08:54.834 --> 08:56.667
YOU PEOPLE
WERE SUPPOSED
TO BRING ON THE FUN.

08:58.458 --> 09:00.834
WE COULD ORDER
SOME PIZZAS.

09:00.834 --> 09:01.583
WE COULD
RENT SOME MOVIES.

09:01.583 --> 09:03.250
WE COULD
PLAY STRIP POKER.

09:03.250 --> 09:03.959
All: NO.

09:03.959 --> 09:05.375
OH, COME ON. IT'S NOT LIKE

09:05.375 --> 09:06.542
I HAVEN'T
SEEN YOU ALL NAKED BEFORE.

09:06.542 --> 09:08.875
OK, OK.
WE'LL RENT MOVIES.

09:08.875 --> 09:09.875
[SNEEZES]

09:09.875 --> 09:10.875
BLESS YOU!

09:10.875 --> 09:12.291
THANK YOU.

09:12.291 --> 09:13.375
PACE.

09:13.375 --> 09:15.000
THANK YOU.

09:18.166 --> 09:20.500
HEY. WHY DO I
KNOW THAT GUY?

09:20.500 --> 09:20.708
WHO IS HE?

09:24.542 --> 09:26.417
Jen: OH, MY GOD!
IS THAT CHRIS HARTFORD?

09:26.417 --> 09:28.041
OH, MY GOD.

09:28.041 --> 09:30.708
THE MOVIE STAR I ORDERED
FROM MY TEEN BEAT  CATALOG

09:30.708 --> 09:32.000
FINALLY GOT HERE.
I WAS SO WORRIED.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.375
AUDREY!

09:34.375 --> 09:36.333
I WAS HOPING
YOU'D BE HERE.

09:36.333 --> 09:38.750
CHRIS. WOW. HEY.
HOW ARE YOU?

09:40.417 --> 09:43.041
SHE'S HUGGING
A MOVIE STAR.

09:43.041 --> 09:44.250
IT'S SO WEIRD.

09:44.250 --> 09:47.417
I'M SORRY. YOU GUYS,
THIS IS MY FRIEND CHRIS.

09:47.417 --> 09:49.792
CHRIS, THESE ARE
ALL MY FRIENDS FROM COLLEGE.

09:49.792 --> 09:52.125
HEY. CHRIS.

09:52.125 --> 09:52.708
JACK.

09:52.708 --> 09:53.583
WE'RE NOT FAMOUS.

09:53.583 --> 09:55.917
HOW DO YOU GUYS
KNOW EACH OTHER?

09:55.917 --> 09:59.208
WELL, WE WENT TO
HIGH SCHOOL TOGETHER.

09:59.208 --> 10:00.375
WE WENT TO THE SAME SCHOOL.

10:00.375 --> 10:03.125
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

10:03.125 --> 10:06.792
WELL, MTV's SPONSORING
THIS CONCERT AT A HOTEL
A COUPLE BLOCKS DOWN.

10:06.792 --> 10:09.667
IT'S THIS NEW BAND, M2M.
YOU GUYS KNOW 'EM?

10:09.667 --> 10:10.917
YEAH! MARIT AND MARION
FROM NORWAY.

10:10.917 --> 10:13.500
MARIT'S FAVORITE FOOD
IS CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP,

10:13.500 --> 10:16.291
WHERE MARION
PREFERS ORANGE FANTA
AS HER DRINK OF CHOICE.

10:16.291 --> 10:18.083
[CHUCKLING]

10:18.083 --> 10:20.959
ANYWAYS,
GAVE ME FREE TICKETS

10:20.959 --> 10:22.083
IF YOU GUYS
WANT TO GO.

10:22.083 --> 10:23.750
ACTUALLY, WE WERE
JUST MAKING THESE PLANS.

10:23.750 --> 10:25.750
[COUGHING]

10:29.166 --> 10:30.333
OR, YOU KNOW,

10:30.333 --> 10:32.166
WE COULD GO TO
A BIG MTV CONCERT,

10:32.166 --> 10:33.250
'CAUSE THAT'S COOL, TOO.

10:33.250 --> 10:35.625
GREAT.
I'LL LEAD THE WAY.

10:35.625 --> 10:37.875
IS IT TRUE THAT YOU'RE DATING
JENNIFER LOVE HEWITT?

10:39.208 --> 10:40.375
SO--

10:40.375 --> 10:41.792
DON'T EVEN
BOTHER ASKING,

10:41.792 --> 10:43.458
BECAUSE
THE ANSWER IS NO.

10:43.458 --> 10:45.125
REALLY? DIDN'T MAKE
THE TOP 5?

10:45.125 --> 10:46.125
WE WERE FRIENDS.
GOD.

10:46.125 --> 10:48.625
WHAT DO I LOOK LIKE,
THE WHORE OF BABYLON?

10:48.625 --> 10:51.000
DON'T ANSWER
THAT QUESTION.

10:51.000 --> 10:53.291
GO. I'M GONNA WAIT
FOR JOEY.

10:54.875 --> 10:56.083
THAT'S CHRIS.

10:57.458 --> 10:59.333
CHRIS AS IN...

10:59.333 --> 11:00.917
THE ONE.
THE ONE WHO I THINK OF

11:00.917 --> 11:01.792
EVERY TIME IN YOUR EYES
COMES ON THE RADIO.

11:01.792 --> 11:05.291
MY PERFECT HIGH SCHOOL
BOYFRIEND

11:05.291 --> 11:06.625
WHO EVERY OTHER BOY
GETS COMPARED TO,

11:06.625 --> 11:07.834
AND WHO NO ONES
LIVED UP TO YET.

11:07.834 --> 11:09.000
YEAH, THAT'S HIM.
HE'S HERE.

11:09.000 --> 11:10.166
KILL ME NOW.

11:10.166 --> 11:11.291
WHY--WHY DID YOU TELL PACEY
HE'S JUST A FRIEND?

11:11.291 --> 11:13.166
I HAD TO.

11:13.166 --> 11:14.667
PACEY AND I
ARE ON THE CUSP

11:14.667 --> 11:16.375
OF FIGURING OUT
OUR WHOLE THING,

11:16.375 --> 11:19.291
AND IF HE KNEW
THAT CHRIS WAS THE LOVE
OF MY YOUNG LIFE,

11:19.291 --> 11:21.125
IT WOULD JUST GET
ALL KINDS OF CONFUSING.

11:21.125 --> 11:22.417
BUT LYING TO HIM
WILL MAKE IT ALL BETTER.

11:22.417 --> 11:23.333
HEY, MOTHER THERESA,

11:23.333 --> 11:25.083
WHY DON'T YOU GO
TAKE A SMOKE BREAK

11:25.083 --> 11:26.917
AND BRING BACK
MY GOOD FRIEND JOEY.

11:26.917 --> 11:28.333
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M SORRY.

11:28.333 --> 11:29.708
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

11:29.708 --> 11:31.500
I NEED TO GO THROW UP.

11:31.500 --> 11:33.333
OH, NO.
IT'LL BE OK.

11:33.333 --> 11:34.542
I'M GONNA GO CHANGE.

11:34.542 --> 11:34.917
OK. I'LL BE HERE.

11:38.375 --> 11:41.041
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

11:42.291 --> 11:42.917
HELLO?

11:42.917 --> 11:45.166
Charlie: JOEY POTTER.

11:45.166 --> 11:46.750
YOU AGAIN.

11:46.750 --> 11:47.667
THAT'S RIGHT.

11:47.667 --> 11:49.500
I WAS STARTING
TO FEEL LIKE

11:49.500 --> 11:50.917
WE WERE ESTRANGED
OR SOMETHING.

11:50.917 --> 11:52.041
WELL, YOU KNOW,

11:52.041 --> 11:55.208
I'M JUST DOING MY BEST
TO TRACK YOU DOWN.

11:55.208 --> 11:56.917
HOW'D YOU MAKE OUT?

11:56.917 --> 11:59.625
WELL, NOT TOO BAD,
ACTUALLY.

11:59.625 --> 12:01.041
REALLY?

12:01.041 --> 12:02.625
NO.

12:05.166 --> 12:07.667
I'LL CALL YOU
RIGHT BACK.

12:15.041 --> 12:16.083
[CROWD CHEERING]

12:16.083 --> 12:17.834
Woman: ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT TO?

12:17.834 --> 12:18.959
I APPRECIATE YOUR OFFER,
BUT I'M HERE WITH SOMEBODY.

12:18.959 --> 12:21.375
I DON'T SEE HER
NEXT TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

12:21.375 --> 12:24.000
OCCASIONALLY,
I HAVE TO LET HER
MINGLE WITH THE PEOPLE.

12:24.000 --> 12:25.083
I'M GOOD THAT WAY.

12:25.083 --> 12:26.917
DON'T LEAVE.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

12:26.917 --> 12:28.417
I HAVE TO DO SOMETHING.

12:30.542 --> 12:31.792
WOMEN, RIGHT,
THEY JUST WILL NOT
TAKE "NO" FOR AN ANSWER.

12:31.792 --> 12:33.750
I MEAN, WHO DOES
SHE THINK SHE IS?

12:33.750 --> 12:35.625
HELLO, MIAMI!

12:35.625 --> 12:39.041
OH, THAT'S WHO SHE IS.

12:39.041 --> 12:41.917
♪ IT'S BEEN 9 DAYS,
8 HOURS ♪

12:41.917 --> 12:44.250
♪ 40 MINUTES,
10 SECONDS ♪

